VALUES ('16abe0fd-34eb-49d0-9dcd-78bc5a4ec5c1', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'The initial randomized trial failed to detect a statistically reliable effect despite adequate sample size and pre-registered analysis plans. ______ the replication study, which enrolled additional participants and extended the observation window by six months, revealed a robust pattern consistent with the researchers'' preregistered hypothesis.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Complicating the binary the author has established,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Complicating the binary the author has established, This participial phrase matches the rhetorical relationship between the two clauses: it signals contrast while preserving sentence grammar. Hard Digital SAT transition items expect syntactic embedding rather than a bare adverb. The following clause must read as a grammatically complete continuation."},{"id":"B","text":"Building directly on the mechanism described above,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Building directly on the mechanism described above, This phrase suggests contrast, which misaligns with how the prior and following clauses relate. Hard transition items punish single-word pivots when the logic requires a fuller rhetorical bridge between contrasting trial outcomes."},{"id":"C","text":"Reinforcing the cumulative case the passage has assembled,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Reinforcing the cumulative case the passage has assembled, This phrase suggests contrast, which misaligns with how the prior and following clauses relate. Hard transition items punish single-word pivots when the logic requires a fuller rhetorical bridge between contrasting trial outcomes."},{"id":"D","text":"Illustrating the abstract claim with a concrete case,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Illustrating the abstract claim with a concrete case, This phrase suggests contrast, which misaligns with how the prior and following clauses relate. Hard transition items punish single-word pivots when the logic requires a fuller rhetorical bridge between contrasting trial outcomes."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'The two clauses contrast a null initial trial with a successful replication. Hard transition items require a participial or clausal bridge—not a single adverb—that signals contrast while grammatically modifying the subject of the following clause. The passage anchors the correct choice in language such as "The initial randomized trial failed to detect a statistically reliable effect despite adequate sampl…", which eliminates options that contradict or overreach that evidence. Choice A is correct because it aligns with the textual logic: Complicating the binary the author has established,. Each incorrect option either contradicts an explicit detail, imports information absent from the stimulus, or answers a different question than the stem asks. On hard Digital SAT items, the best answer synthesizes multiple sentences rather than matching a single keyword in isolation.', NULL, 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"hard_content_v2","original":true,"explanation_v2":true,"hard_content_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
